FIGURE 5.
Photomicrographs of 

Myxodavisia

sp.
from the gall bladder of 

Serranus scriba

. (A) Mature spores in sutural view presenting the spherical polar capsules (
pc
) and the straight to slightly curved suture line (
sl
). (B–D) Fresh smear of mature spores with variable forms. (E) Mature spore showing the sporoplasmic nuclei (
sn
) and the Capsulogenic nucleus (
cn
). (F–J) Fresh mature spores in apical view, notice the presence of sutural ridges (
sr
) in both posterior and anterior ends and the lateral appendages (
la
). Scale bar = 20 µm in D, 10 µm in A–C,E–J.
